\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki walked behind Mrs. Azuki, her footsteps echoing softly in the quiet hallway. The teacher\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s kind demeanor and gentle guidance reminded her of Mrs. Kitagawa, the teacher who had taken her from the Art Club in the present. The memory was bittersweet, a sharp pang of longing cutting through her chest.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 She thought about her weekly plein-air sessions with the Art Club, the way the sunlight would filter through the trees as she painted, the laughter and camaraderie of her fellow club members. She thought about her father, standing at the end of that hallway in the present, his stern expression as he told her it was time to leave the club behind. That had been the last day of her life as she knew it\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the day her dreams had been taken from her.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 But now, standing in this strange yet familiar version of her school, it felt like a whole new beginning. Everything was the same, yet different. The walls, the floors, the air\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it all carried a sense of nostalgia, as if she had stepped into a memory she didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know she had.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Mrs. Azuki stopped in front of a door, her hand resting on the handle. Haruki looked up and saw the sign above it:\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 A1}{\f0\fs24\b0 . Her heart skipped a beat. This was her classroom\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 or at least, the 1960s version of it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Here we are,\u8221\'94 Mrs. Azuki said, her voice warm and reassuring. \u8220\'93This is your classroom, Class 1A. I\u8217\'92ll introduce you to the teacher, and then you can take a seat.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Mrs. Azuki gently opened the door and peeked inside, interrupting the lesson with a soft knock. The teacher\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a tall, stern-looking man with glasses perched on the bridge of his nose\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 paused mid-sentence and turned to the door. Mrs. Azuki whispered something to him, gesturing toward Haruki. The teacher nodded, his expression serious but not unkind.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 He turned back to the class, his voice firm and commanding. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Class, we will be joined by a new student today. Please welcome her properly.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Mrs. Azuki stepped aside and motioned for Haruki to enter. Haruki took a deep breath, straightened her uniform, and stepped into the classroom. All eyes turned to her, the students sitting upright in their seats, their hands neatly folded on their desks. The atmosphere was formal, almost rigid, a stark contrast to the more relaxed environment she was used to in the present.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The teacher gestured for Haruki to stand at the front of the class. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Introduce yourself,\u8221\'94 he said, his tone leaving no room for hesitation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki swallowed hard, her voice trembling slightly as she spoke. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My name is Haruki Fujiyama. I\u8217\'92m\u8230\'85 pleased to meet you all.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The class responded in unison, their voices loud and clear. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Welcome, Haruki-san!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The teacher nodded, seemingly satisfied with the introduction. He pointed to an empty seat near the back of the room. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You may take your seat there, Fujiyama.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki bowed slightly, a gesture of respect she had seen in old movies but never practiced herself, and made her way to the desk. The students watched her with polite curiosity, their gazes following her as she walked. She sat down, her hands resting on the wooden desk, and glanced around the room.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The classroom was smaller than she remembered, the desks arranged in neat, orderly rows. The walls were lined with wooden panels, and the blackboard at the front was framed by brass trim. The air smelled of chalk and polished wood, a far cry from the faint scent of plastic and metal that permeated her school in the present.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As the teacher resumed the lesson, Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mind wandered. She thought about Nagano and his friends, about the strict Mr. Genzo, about the strange, surreal world she had found herself in. She didn\u8217\'92t know what the future held, but one thing was clear: she couldn\u8217\'92t go back. Not yet.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 For now, all she could do was take it one step at a time.}
