\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The current lesson being taught was chemistry. The teacher stood at the front of the room, writing equations on the blackboard with precise, deliberate strokes. Haruki sat at her desk, her notebook open in front of her, but her mind was elsewhere.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 For the first time since arriving in this strange version of her school, she felt a flicker of normalcy. She was a student, sitting in a classroom, listening to a lesson. It was familiar, almost comforting. But as she glanced around the room, a part of her expected to see her best friends, Aiko and Akihito, sitting nearby, ready to pass her a note or share a joke. Instead, she was met with the faces of strangers\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 students who wouldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t be born for decades in her own time.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The realization hit her like a punch to the gut. She sighed, leaning forward and resting her chin in her hand. But before she could sink too deeply into her thoughts, the teacher\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s sharp voice cut through the air.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Fujiyama,\u8221\'94 he said, his tone firm but not unkind. \u8220\'93Sit properly, please.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki straightened immediately, her cheeks flushing with embarrassment. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes, sir,\u8221\'94 she murmured, adjusting her posture and folding her hands neatly on her desk. The other students didn\u8217\'92t react, their attention focused on the lesson, but Haruki couldn\u8217\'92t help feeling out of place.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The teacher continued the lesson, his voice steady and authoritative. Haruki tried to focus, but her mind kept wandering. She missed Aiko\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s quick wit and Akihito\u8217\'92s quiet support. She missed the Art Club, the freedom to create, the sense of belonging she had found there. But here, in this time, those things didn\u8217\'92t exist\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 at least, not yet.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 When the lesson ended, the teacher announced a class assignment. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You will work in pairs,\u8221\'94 he said, his tone leaving no room for argument. \u8220\'93Complete the problems on page 42 and submit your answers by the end of the period.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The students began pairing up, their movements quick and efficient. Haruki hesitated, unsure of what to do. She didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know anyone in the class, and the thought of approaching a stranger made her stomach twist with anxiety.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 But then the girl seated next to her\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a quiet, serious-looking student with her hair tied back in a neat braid\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 turned to her and nodded. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You can work with me,\u8221\'94 she said, her voice soft but firm.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki blinked, surprised by the offer. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thank you,\u8221\'94 she said, her voice barely above a whisper.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The girl nodded again, opening her textbook to the assigned page. She didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t introduce herself at first, simply turning to Haruki and pointing to the problems on the page. \u8220\'93Let\u8217\'92s start with this one,\u8221\'94 she said, her tone matter-of-fact.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki pulled her chair closer to the girl\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s desk, her heart still racing. She didn\u8217\'92t know what to expect, but for now, she was grateful for the small act of kindness. The girl began explaining the problem, her voice soft but confident. Haruki tried to follow along, but it quickly became clear that she hadn\u8217\'92t fully grasped the lesson.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The girl noticed Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s confusion and paused, her brow furrowing slightly. \u8220\'93You didn\u8217\'92t understand the lesson, did you?\u8221\'94 she asked, her tone more curious than accusatory.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki flushed, embarrassed. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Not really,\u8221\'94 she admitted, her voice quiet.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The girl smiled, her expression kind. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s okay. You can just follow my lead.\u8221\'94 She began jotting down the steps to solve the problem, her handwriting neat and precise. Haruki copied her work, her mind still reeling from everything that had happened.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 They sat there in silence for a while, the only sound the scratching of their pens on paper. Then, the girl leaned closer and whispered, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hey.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki looked up, surprised. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re Fujiyama, right?\u8221\'94 the girl asked, her voice low so as not to disturb the other students.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki nodded. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Are you perhaps related to Nagano Fujiyama from 2A?\u8221\'94 the girl asked, her tone casual but curious.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki hesitated, her mind racing. How could she explain her connection to Nagano without revealing the truth? Finally, she shook her head. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No,\u8221\'94 she said, her voice firm. \u8220\'93We just share the same surname.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh,\u8221\'94 the girl said, a hint of disappointment in her voice. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m sure there are a lot of people with the name Fujiyama. Sorry, I jumped to conclusions.\u8221\'94 She giggled softly, her cheeks flushing slightly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Then, as if realizing something, the girl\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s eyes widened. \u8220\'93Oh, I\u8217\'92m so sorry! How rude of me\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 I haven\u8217\'92t even introduced myself!\u8221\'94 She reached out her hand, her smile warm and genuine. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m Honoka Aoki. Nice to meet you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart skipped a beat. She stared at the girl, her mind struggling to process what she had just heard. \u8220\'93Honoka\u8230\'85 Fuji\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94 she started to say, then corrected herself. \u8220\'93Honoka Aoki?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The girl nodded, her smile widening. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah. That\u8217\'92s me!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s pen stopped mid-stroke, her hand freezing as realization dawned on her. This girl\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 this kind, easygoing girl who had been helping her with the assignment\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 was her mother. Honoka Aoki. The woman who, in the future, would become her strict, traditional mother, always pushing her to conform to societal expectations.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 But here, in this time, she was just a teenager. A student. A girl who giggled and apologized for being rude. A girl who didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t yet know the weight of the future that awaited her.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s chest tightened, a mix of emotions swirling inside her\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 shock, sadness, and a strange, aching tenderness. She didn\u8217\'92t know what to say or how to act. All she could do was stare at Honoka, her mind racing.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka tilted her head, her expression concerned. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Are you okay? You look like you\u8217\'92ve seen a ghost.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki forced a smile, though her heart was pounding. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m fine,\u8221\'94 she said, her voice shaky. \u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s just\u8230\'85 nice to meet you mo\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0  I mean, Aoki-san.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka smiled, her eyes crinkling at the corners. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Nice to meet you too, Fujiyama-san.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As they returned to their work, Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mind was a whirlwind of thoughts. She didn\u8217\'92t know how she had ended up here, or why, but one thing was clear: she had been given a chance to see her parents as they truly were\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 not as the stern, distant figures she knew, but as the people they had been before life had shaped them.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 And maybe, just maybe, she could change things. For them. For herself.}
